item.description:
The 'Policy Managment' folder in the 'Duo Onboarding' collection provides a set of requests designed to define and assign policies to the newly created Duo account.

Policy configuration and assignment can be complex, but understanding the core functionality of Duo's policy engine and how these policies work together will help in defining granular policy definitions to meet your customer's security needs. If you aren't familiar with Duo's policy stack, please refer to our [Policy and Control](https://duo.com/docs/policy) documentation for further insight. Doing so will help defining the policies within this API playground much more intutive.

Within the workspace, we are using the following endpoints to pull, create, and update policies.

- Retrieve Policies - Retrieve a complete set of all policies. Includes all [policy section data](https://duo.com/docs/adminapi#policy-section-data) for each policy.
- Create Policy - Creates a new custom policy with the `name` specified in the parameters.
- Update Policy - Change an existing policy's `name`, add or remove policy `sections`, or update keys/values for the policy with the specified policy_key
    - If you add a new policy `section` to a custom policy then the API enables the section (that is, makes it active in the policy) and sets the valid values you specify. Any key/value pairs not specified for the section will be set to their default values. If you add a blank policy section, it will be enabled for the policy with default values.If you modify values for an existing policy `section` then the API changes only the values you specify.

#### Defining Policies

While other requests in this workspace use the Params section of the request to define the parameters to be sent to the Duo API, the /policy endpoint accepts the parameters in the body of the request. See the [Duo Admin API - Policy](https://duo.com/docs/adminapi#policy) documentation for further insight.

To make defining polcies as simple as possible within the workspace, we have included several policy templates below. However, if you would like to define more granular and specic policy options, please update the policy sections according to our [Policy Sections Data](https://duo.com/docs/adminapi#policy-section-data) as appropriate for your client's needs.

#### Example Policy Section Data (Do not use)

``` json
{
    "sections": {
        "anonymous_networks": {
            # Values: 1 of no-action, require-mfa, deny
            "anonymous_access_behavior": "no-action"
        },
        "authentication_methods": {
           # "duo-passcode" and "phonecall" are blocked by default
           # values for lists: "desktop", "duo-passcode", "duo-push", "duo-push-pwl", "hardware-token", 
           # "phonecall" (UI: phone callback), "webauthn-platform" (UI: WebAuthn / Touch ID), 
           # "webauthn-platform-pwl","webauthn-roaming" (UI: WebAuthn / security keys (WebAuthn)),     
           # "webauthn-roaming-pwl", "sms"
            "allowed_auth_list": ["duo-push", "hardware-token", "webauthn-platform", "webauthn-roaming", "sms"],
            "blocked_auth_list": ["duo-passcode", "phonecall"],
            "require_verified_push": true,
            # default is 3, values are 3-6
            "verified_push_digits": 3,
        },
        "authentication_policy": {
            # values: 1 of enforce, bypass, deny
            "user_auth_behavior": "enforce"
        },
        "authorized_networks": {
            "no_2fa_required": {
                # IP address lists can contain individual IPs, IP ranges and IP ranges in CIDR notation
                "ip_list": ["1.2.3.4", "5.6.7.8", "57.23.4.1-57.23.4.100", "152.241.10.0/24"],
                # must have at least one IP address in ip_list to change the default require_enrollment
                "require_enrollment": true
            },
            "mfa_required": {
                "ip_list": ["1.2.3.4", "5.6.7.8", "57.23.4.1-57.23.4.100", "152.241.10.0/24"]
            },
            # must have at least one IP address in EITHER or BOTH ip_list(s) to change the default deny_other_access
            "deny_other_access": false
        },
        "browsers": {
            "allowed_browsers_list": ["chrome", "chrome-mobile", "edge", "firefox", "safari", "safari-mobile"],
            "blocked_browsers_list": ["ie", "other-browsers"],
            # Value is 1 of "warn-only", "warn-and-block", "no-remediation"
            # if this value is set, it affects ALL the browsers in the allowed list
            "out_of_date_behavior": "no-remediation",
            # The expected values are shown in the UI, other numerical values are invalid
            "browser_max_ood_days": 30
        },
        "device_health_app": {
            # If an OS is listed in requires_DHA, it's the equivalent of setting "Enforcing" in the UI.
            # "linux" as a value for any key in this block requires setting a feature flag
            "requires_DHA": ["macos", "windows", "linux"],
            "prompt_to_install": ["macos", "windows", "linux"],
            "enforce_firewall": ["macos", "windows", "linux"],                      
            "enforce_encryption": ["macos", "windows", "linux"],
            "enforce_system_password": ["macos", "windows", "linux"],
            # Enforcing a security agent is implied by at least one macos_endpoint_security_list entry
            # Mac endpoint security agent values as listed in the policy modal dropdown
            "macos_endpoint_security_list": ["endpt_agent1", "endpt_agent2"],
            "macos_remediation_note": "some note",                
            # Windows endpoint security agent values as listed in the policy modal dropdown
            "windows_endpoint_security_list": ["endpt_agent1", "endpt_agent2"],
            "windows_remediation_note": "some note"
        },
        "duo_mobile_app": {
            "require_updates": true
        },
        "full_disk_encryption": {
            "require_encryption": false
        },
        "mobile_device_biometrics": {
            "require_biometrics": false
        },
    # called â€œNew User policyâ€ in UI
        "new_user": {
            # Values: 1 of "enroll", "no-mfa", "deny"
            "new_user_behavior": "enroll"
        },
        "operating_systems": {
            # allow and block lists must not contain the same values.
            # allow_os_list contains OSes with no constraints or warnings.
            # block_os_list contains OSes that are not allowed.
            "allow_os_list": ["android", "chromeos", "ios", "linux", "macos", "windows", "unknownos"],
            "block_os_list": ["blackberry", "windowsphone"],
            "os_restrictions": {
                # Defaults for os_restriction blocks: 
                #   Warn and block policies = no-remediation
                #   Warn and block policy versions = "" (blank string)
                #     Versions should be auto-set for anything other than no-remediation (blank) or less-than-version (see below)
                #   Warn and block remediation days = 0
                # Less-than-version - this should require *_version to be filled in with a valid value (not blank).
                "android": {
                    # no-remediation equates to UI values "never" for warn_policy and "none" for block_policy
                    # warn_policy values: "no-remediation", "less-than-latest", "less-than-version", "end-of-life", "not-up-to-date"
                    "warn_policy": "no-remediation",
                    "warn_version": "",
                    # *_remediation_days values come from the list shown in the UI (0, 14, 30, 60, 90, 180, 365)
                    # other values are invalid
                    "warn_remediation_days": 0,
                    # block_policy values: "no-remediation", "less-than-latest", "less-than-version", "end-of-life", "not-up-to-date"
                    "block_policy": "no-remediation",    
                    "block_version": "",
                    "block_remediation_days": 0
                },
                # see android_restrictions for notes
                "ios": {
                     "warn_policy": "no-remediation",
                    "warn_version": "",
                    "warn_remediation_days": 0,
                    "block_policy": "no-remediation",
                    "block_version": "",
                    "block_remediation_days": 0
                },
                # see android_restrictions for notes
                "macos": {
                     "warn_policy": "no-remediation",
                    "warn_version": "",
                    "warn_remediation_days": 0,
                    "block_policy": "no-remediation",
                    "block_version": "",
                    "block_remediation_days": 0
                },
                # see android_restrictions for notes
                "windows": {
                     "warn_policy": "no-remediation",
                    "warn_version": "",
                    "warn_remediation_days": 0,
                    "block_policy": "no-remediation",
                    "block_version": "",
                    "block_remediation_days": 0
                }
            }
        },
        "plugins": {
            # Values: 1 of "allow-all" or "block-all"
            "flash": "block-all",
            # Values: 1 of "allow-all", "warn-only", "warn-and-block", "block-all"
            "java": "warn-only",
            # The expected values are shown in the UI, other values are invalid
            "java_max_ood_days": 30
        },
        "remembered_devices": {
            "browser_apps": {
                "enabled": true,
                # Values: 1 of "user-based" or "risk-based"
                "remember_method": "user-based",
                "user_based": {
                    # Values: 1 of "days" or "hours"
                    "max_time_units": "hours",
                    # max_time_value can be 1-365 (if units are days) OR 1-8760 (if units are hours)
                    "max_time_value": 12,
                    "confirm_per_app": false
                },
                "risk_based": {
                    # Values: 1 of "days" or "hours"
                    "max_time_units": "days"
                    # max_time_value can be 1-365 (if days) OR 1-8760 (if hours),       
                    "max_time_value": 30,
                }
            },
            "windows_logon": {
                "enabled": true,
                # Values: 1 of "days" or "hours"
                "max_time_units": "days",
                # max_time_value can be 1-365 (if days) OR 1-8760 (if hours)
                "max_time_value": 30,
            }
        },
        "risk_based_factor_selection": {
            "limit_to_risk_based_auth_methods": false,
            # default is 3, values are 3-6
            "risk_based_verified_push_digits": 3
        },
        "screen_lock": {
            "require_screen_lock": true
        },
        "tampered_devices": {
            "block_tampered_devices": true
        },
        "trusted_endpoints": {
            # Values are 1 of allow-all, require-trusted, no-action 
            #  "no-action" (UI: "Do not check endpoints for trustworthiness" option is checked) is dependent on 
            #   whether a feature flag is ON
            "trusted_endpoint_checking": "allow-all",
            "cisco_secure_endpoint_can_block": false,
            # values are 1 of allow-all, require-trusted, (and no-action, if a feature flag as mentioned above is set)
            # setting a value is optional â€“ auto-sets to the same value as trusted_endpoint_checking
            "trusted_endpoint_checking_mobile": "allow-all"
        },
        "user_location": {
            "require_mfa_countries_list": ["countrycode1","countrycode2"],
            "deny_access_countries_list": ["countrycode1","countrycode2"],
            "allow_access_no_2fa_countries_list": ["countrycode1","countrycode2"],
            # listed as "no action" in the UI
            "ignore_location_countries_list": ["countrycode1","countrycode2"], 
            # Values are 1 of ignore-location, require-mfa, deny-access, allow-access-no-2fa
            "default_action": "ignore-location"
        }

 ```

